      <section eId="sec_13_2_2">
        <num>13-2-2</num>
        <content>
          <p>The following rules, among others, shall be used in arriving at the true interpretation of contracts:</p>
          <p>(Orig. Code 1863, §§ 1, 2721; Code 1868, §§ 1, 2715; Code 1873, § 1, 2757; Code 1882, §§ 1, 2757; Civil Code 1895, §§ 1, 3675; Civil Code 1910, §§ 1, 4268; Code 1933, § 20-704; Ga. L. 1962, p. 156, § 1; Ga. L. 1963, p. 188, § 38; Ga. L. 1964, p. 414, § 1; Ga. L. 2010, p. 878, § 13/HB 1387.)</p>
          <p>The 2010 amendment,
      effective June 3, 2010, part of an Act to revise, modernize, and correct the Code, added "and" at the end of paragraph (8).</p>
        </content>
